Key CSS Properties Explained:
object-fit: cover; - Ensures the image covers the entire container while maintaining aspect ratio (might crop the image)

object-position: center; - Centers the image within the container

height: 100vh; - Makes the container full viewport height

width: 100%; - Makes the image take full width of its container

overflow: hidden; - Prevents any overflow beyond the container

Which Solution to Choose?
Solution 1 (Background image) is best if you don't need the image for SEO or accessibility

Solution 2/3 (Object-fit) is best if you need the image as an actual <img> tag for SEO or want to add alt text

Solution 4 uses Bootstrap classes for a cleaner HTML approach

Choose based on your specific needs. The object-fit: cover approach (Solution 2/3) is usually the most reliable for <img> tags.

